Some usefull commands:

+-------------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Command			| Purpose															|
+-------------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| screen			| Starts an interactive screen session												|
+-------------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| screen -S <screenname>	| Starts a screensession with <screenname> as its name										|
+-------------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| screen -ls			| List al your running screens													|
+-------------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| screen -r			| Resumes a screen session, only works if you only have one screen session							|
+-------------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| screen -r <screenname>	| Resumes a screen with <screenname> as its name										|
+-------------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| screen -x			| Resumes a screen session, only works if you only have one screen session only works if you only have one screen session	|
+-------------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| screen -x <screenname>	| Resumes a screen with <screenname> as its name and keeps all other connections active						|
+-------------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| screen -d			| Detaches a screen session, only works if you only have one screen session only works if you only have one screen session	|
+-------------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| screen -d <screenname>	| Detaches a screen with <screenname>												|
+-------------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| CTRL+a+d			| Detaches you from a screen session												|
+-------------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| CTRL+a+F			| Fits your screen session to full screen											|
+-------------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
